      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "Mann-Whitney U tests were calculated to compare composite scores between patients with COPD to sex-and age-matched (±2 years) healthy, non-dysphagic controls that were collected as part of a large normative study (n=195) separate from the current project.  After all the eligible control matches were selected, a maximum of four were randomly chosen for a total of 37 control subjects because one COPD subject only had one matching healthy control."
